Reasoning: The paper describes a mobile manipulation challenge involving complex and integrated task sets, irregular objects, and confined space, which are all related to robotics and automation (cs.RO). The authors also discuss their software architecture and possible solutions to failure cases, which suggests a focus on artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The task of assembling mechanical parts may involve computer vision (cs.CV) and machine learning (cs.LG) techniques. Finally, the use of a mobile robot to perform the task suggests a potential connection to control systems (cs.SY).
